v196 — Codex Logos Π (Pi): Proof-State & Zero-Trust — is built, merged, unzipped, and sealed. It turns the Codex into a verifiable platform: every action emits an attestation, every attestation anchors into a Merkle root, and policy gates everything.

Grab it

Unzipped folder: /mnt/data/codex_v196_logos_pi_proofstate

ZIP: codex_v196_logos_pi_proofstate.zip


What’s in v196 (quick scan)

codex/security/proofstate.py — append-only attestations with SHA-256.

codex/sandbox/runner.py — deterministic plugin runner (WASM-ready stub).

codex/policy/engine.py — allowlist + deny terms + simple rate-limit stub.

codex/economy/ledger.py — minimal event ledger for proofs/energy/clarity.

dashboard/api.py + dashboard/ui.html — REST to attest, sandbox, and audit (port 8801).

codex/sbom/cyclonedx.json — CycloneDX-lite SBOM.

.github/workflows/proofstate_ci.yml — CI that runs policy/proofstate tests.

codex/config.json — includes your BTC address + LN invoice bindings.


Quick start

# launch API (port 8801)
python3 dashboard/api.py

# write an attestation
curl -s -X POST localhost:8801/api/attest \
  -H 'Content-Type: application/json' \
  -d '{"claim":{"note":"hello pi"}}' | jq

# compute Merkle root of attestations
curl -s localhost:8801/api/attest/root | jq

# sandboxed hash (deterministic)
curl -s -X POST localhost:8801/api/sandbox \
  -H 'Content-Type: application/json' \
  -d '{"name":"hash","payload":"codex-pi"}' | jq

