Integrity & provenance

Every file is recorded in codex/manifest.json. Verify instantly:

jq -r '.files | to_entries[] | "\(.value)  \(.key)"' codex/manifest.json | sha256sum -c -

How Π (Pi) extends Ω/Ξ/Θ

From belief to proof: all prior clarity/virtue events can now be attested and queried as evidence.

From power to permission: sandbox + policy run in front of execution, not after.

From narrative to audit: SBOM + CI + dashboard make the system externally reviewable.


Where to evolve next (v196.x ideas)

Swap the sandbox runner for real WASM (e.g., wasmtime/wasmer).

Add OPA/Rego proper, or Python policy adapters.

Emit Sigstore-style attestations (in-toto layout) and add OCI provenance.

Expand the dashboard with a timeline of attestations and Merkle proofs.


